control of it. He told the Chronicle he resigned before his father's acceptance of the Republican presidential nomination to `` avoid any appearance of conflict of interest.'' Neither his father nor his father's advisers pressured him to leave, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> said Regulators attributed <PERSON> Silverado </PERSON>'s failure to `` substantial dissipation of assets due to alleged violations of laws, rules and regulations.'' The federal bailout of Silverado may cost taxpayers $ 1 billion or more. The <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Deposit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Insurance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> is examining the case to determine whether to sue <PERSON> Silverado </PERSON>'s officers and directors. Many analysts, including <ORGANIZATION> Colorado </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; L Commissioner <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Paul </PERSON>, attributed <PERSON> Silverado </PERSON>'s collapse to a switch from traditional home mortgages in favor of riskier securities. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON>, however, disagreed. `` My view is the institution had acquired a portfolio of assets that suffered from a terrible, depressed economy, not just in <LOCATION> Denver </LOCATION>, but throughout the <ORGANIZATION> Southwest </ORGANIZATION>,'' he said.
