<DATELINE>DHAKA, Bangladesh (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Police raided the hideout of a self-proclaimed Moslem saint whose followers captured one of their colleagues, and at least 27 people died in the ensuing gunbattle Wednesday, officials said. The captive officer and three other policemen were among those killed in the fight that began late Tuesday in <LOCATION> Pakundia </LOCATION> village. It ended at dawn Wednesday with the arrest of <PERSON> Matiur </PERSON> <PERSON> Rahman </PERSON>, a former army major who now calls himself a Pir or saint, police officials said. Twenty other people were wounded, said the officials in <LOCATION> Pakundia </LOCATION>, about 50 miles north of <LOCATION> Dhaka </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Kishoreganj </LOCATION> district. They said the raid was ordered to free the policeman held captive by <PERSON> Rahman </PERSON>'s supporters in the hideout, located in a sprawling building complex. The policeman had gone to the hideout Monday to investigate reports of `` anti-social activities by the <PERSON> Pir </PERSON>'s followers,'' an official said. He did not say what the anti-social activities were but it was believed to be a reference to gambling and selling drugs. <PERSON> Rahman </PERSON>'s 16 disciples also were arrested and 30 others surrendered after the raid by about 700 policemen, they said. Earlier, at least 12 people were reported killed, but a search team found 15 more bodies inside the hideout Wednesday, the officials said. Self-proclaimed Pirs, who profess to cure physical ailments and prescribe ways to becoming rich, abound in <LOCATION> Bangladesh </LOCATION>, a nation of 110 million people. About 88 percent of them are Moslems. President <PERSON> Hussain </PERSON> <PERSON> Muhammad </PERSON> <PERSON> Ershad </PERSON>, a former army general, is a follower of a popular god <PERSON> Hashmatullah </PERSON>, who claims to have thousands of disciples. Hashmataullah is based at <LOCATION> Atroshi </LOCATION> in <LOCATION> Faridpur </LOCATION> district, 40 miles west of <LOCATION> Dha