<HEAD>Surprise: White House Chief of Staff Lauds Administration</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CHRISTOPHER CONNELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 White House Chief of Staff <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> H. </PERSON> <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON> confessed to the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Club </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday that the <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> administration has made a lot of mistakes, some of them unreported `` doozies.'' Thus ended his confession. <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON> not only refused to shed light on the flubs, but devoted most of an hour to a glowing review of the administration, five weeks shy of its first birthday, that left practically no superlative unsaid. He called <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> `` probably the most underrated man in modern history to serve in the presidency.'' <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON>, who said his aim was to influence the journalists' year-end analyses, said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> is getting raves, too, in polls that show his approval ratings in the mid-to-high 70s, `` numbers that truly are virtually unprecedented in history. From the savings and loan bailout to the war on drugs, <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has set the agenda and shown an ability to work with the Democrat-controlled <ORGANIZATION> Congress </ORGANIZATION> without sacrificing his principles, the former <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hampshire </LOCATION> governor argued. <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has `` really excelled'' in shaping and encouraging the dramatic changes toward democracy in the Soviet bloc, <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON> said. `` It was not an easy year. <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> just made it seem easy,'' said <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON>. He said <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> has resisted the temptation to make `` instant'' foreign policy or `` snap conclusions.'' `` The one thing the president understands is that you do n't get extra credit for running out and doing it immediately on television,'' he said. He has handled the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> bloc changes `` as one would handle