TION>. The administration has seldom seen internal quarrels spill out into the press, and <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON> was asked how the White House managed that, a rare achievement in recent administrations. `` It has a calm, low-keyed mild-mannered chief of staff who does n't get upset at anything,'' said the imperious <PERSON> Sununu </PERSON>, evoking laughter _ loudest from his own aides. Any regrets? `` We've made a lot of mistakes. A couple of them you've caught. Most of them you have n't. ... There have been some doozies that you missed.'' Mmmmm. How about an example? His lips are sealed, and he added, `` I'm not even going to write a book.''
