<HEAD>Historical Court Decides Mr. and Mrs. Claus Share Honors</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto FX2</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JACK SCHREIBMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 In a decision <PERSON> Solomon </PERSON> might admire, a judge Wednesday authorized Mrs. <PERSON> Santa </PERSON> <PERSON> Claus </PERSON> to share equal gift-giving Christmas rights with her famous husband, and declared their sleigh `` community property.'' Furthermore, Mrs. <PERSON> Claus </PERSON>' title is now `` Ms.,'' and she is `` emancipated from any household duties'' so that she may accompany her jolly spouse on his airborne tours of the world, according to the ruling by <ORGANIZATION> Municipal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> Judge <PERSON> George </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Choppelas </PERSON>. Christmas generosity symbolized by <PERSON> Santa </PERSON> <PERSON> Claus </PERSON> is a `` universal phenomenon'' and should have no gender strings attached, the judge added, undoubtedly with an eye to his political future. A courtroom jammed with spectators, reporters and photographers broke into cheers and applause at the conclusion of a rather unruly and holiday-happy 60th session of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION>'s mock <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Historical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Review </ORGANIZATION>. The just-for-fun court is a 14-year <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> tradition staged in a real City Hall courtroom, with a real judge, real lawyers, clerks and stenographers. Only the witnesses are phony. Everybody has a good time with such questions as who invented the martini, is chicken soup Jewish penicillin, and where did chop suey come from. `` Thank you for not starting without me,'' said the judge to the trial advocates, <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> Supervisor <PERSON> Angela </PERSON> <PERSON> Alioto </PERSON>, who said <LOCATION> Santa </LOCATION> was a woman, and Public Defender <PERSON> Jeff </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>, who said he must remain a male. <P