<HEAD>Autopsy Awaited on Man Mauled by Dogs</HEAD>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> DULZURA </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION> _ The death of a man apparently mauled by a pack of dogs could lead to a criminal investigation of the animals' owners, whose fearful neighbors had complained about marauding dogs, the sheriff's office said Preliminary findings of the autopsy Wednesday will be available Thursday morning, but if it attributes 69-year-old <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON>'s death to the dogs, the criminal probe would ensue, Sheriff's Lt. <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Tenwolde </PERSON> said Wednesday `` A lot of questions need to be asked before we can speculate about what the outcome is going to be,'' <PERSON> Tenwolde </PERSON> said. On Tuesday, <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> was attacked near the <PERSON> Charles </PERSON> <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> <PERSON> Ranch </PERSON>, where the dogs apparently lived, while he was walking to work. <PERSON> Duarte </PERSON> was unavailable for comment, but his wife, <PERSON> Cindy </PERSON>, said: `` It has never happened before. I ca n't imagine what happened.'' <PERSON> Bill </PERSON> <PERSON> Delany </PERSON>, caretaker of the <LOCATION> Monahan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ranch </LOCATION> where <PERSON> Johnson </PERSON> worked, found the body after driving to pick up his newspaper at his mailbox off the highway. `` It was unbelievable,'' <PERSON> Delany </PERSON> said. `` He appeared to have been eaten alive. That's the only way to describe it. He was eaten alive. I just knew he was gone.'' <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Slough </PERSON>, an off-duty <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION> policeman who lives nearby, went to investigate what he thought was a dogfight and found two dogs picking at the body. They attacked him and he shot and killed one and wounded another, police said. <PERSON> Sally </PERSON> <PERSON> Hazzard </PERSON>, head of the <ORGANIZATION> San </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Diego </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> County </ORGANIZ