Angeles </LOCATION> and was preparing to return to her home north of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. She wanted to get back in time to see daughter <PERSON> Lily </PERSON>, 7, perform in `` The Nutcracker'' with the <LOCATION> Stamford </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Ballet </LOCATION>. <PERSON> Clayburgh </PERSON> is married to playwright <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Rabe </PERSON> and has a 4-year-old son, <PERSON> Michael </PERSON>, and a 17-year-old stepson, <PERSON> Jason </PERSON>. She has starred in such feature films as `` An Unmarried Woman,'' `` Silver Streak,'' `` Starting Over,'' `` <PERSON> Luna </PERSON>,'' `` First Monday in October,'' `` I'm Dancing As Fast As I Can,'' and `` <PERSON> Portnoy </PERSON>'s Complaint. Her last film, `` Shy People'' in 1987, took her to <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>. She played a photojournalist doing a story in the bayou country. `` It was incredibly difficult because we had to go in and out by boat,'' she recalls. `` It was humid and the mosquitoes were terrible. But I loved the people and the wonderful Cajun culture.'' Lately, she's been working more in television. She has a movie for <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>, `` Unspeakable Acts,'' based on a child abuse case. She plays a psychologist who finds a way to interview the children without influencing their testimony. Past TV movies include `` Hustling,'' `` <PERSON> Griffin </PERSON> and <LOCATION> Phoenix </LOCATION>: A Love Story,'' `` Miles To Go'' and `` Who Gets the Friends.'' `` I've been offered series but I've turned them down,'' she said. `` I'm not ready yet to put in that much time away from the kids. I am looking into a few comedy series for the future. I'm very happy doing TV movies, however, and I may not do a series at all `` Doing a series is steady work and comedy is a lot of fun. Comedy is something you do n't get in a TV movie. Also, the idea of working with an audience doing a series is very appealing.''
