n the <ORGANIZATION> Tribune </ORGANIZATION> report. <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION> officials have said the pilots were given the proposal more than a week ago. United pilots have not publicly stated their opinion of the plan but their leader, <PERSON> Frederick </PERSON> <PERSON> Dubinsky </PERSON>, said last week his union would not be rushed into a transaction. <PERSON> Patricia </PERSON> <PERSON> Friend </PERSON>, president of the <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> flight attendants' union, said they were given the proposal last week and are still studying it <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s board is under pressure from the investor group <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Partners </ORGANIZATION>, which owns 11.8 percent of <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s stock, to sell or otherwise restructure the company to boost share prices. <PERSON> Keith </PERSON> <PERSON> Gollust </PERSON>, a general partner in <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION>, declined comment Tuesday on whether the New York-based partnership would support the reported buyout plan. <ORGANIZATION> Coniston </ORGANIZATION> has threatened to launch a drive for shareholder consent to dump 13 of <ORGANIZATION> UAL </ORGANIZATION>'s 15 directors and create a five-member board.
