<HEAD>Grain Markets Open Little Changed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Grain and soybean futures prices were narrowly mixed in early trading today on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION>, with wheat and soybeans mostly lower and corn mostly higher. The slight drop in soybean values largely reflected weakening in the soybean meal and oil markets and expectations for continued slow export demand, analysts said. Contracts for soybean deliveries next fall gained slightly, though, on reports of severe dryness in southern <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION>, the world's second-largest soybean producer. Wheat was down slightly amid perceptions of slackening demand and ideas the market was due for a downward correction after its recent gains. The <ORGANIZATION> Agriculture </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Deparment </ORGANIZATION>'s rejection of several bids for export wheat also weighed on futures. Corn futures were mostly higher in line with the cash market, following Tuesday's <ORGANIZATION> USDA </ORGANIZATION> announcement that the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION> had bought about 100,000 metric tons of <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION> corn. Sharply lower precious metal prices contributed to the markets' overall bearish cast, said <PERSON> Joel </PERSON> <PERSON> Karlin </PERSON>, an analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Research </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> In early trading, wheat futures were \ cent to 1 -LCB- cents lower with the contract for delivery in December at $ 4.12 a bushel; corn was -LCB- cent lower to 1 \ cents higher with December at $ 2.34 \ a bushel; oats were unchanged to -LCB- cent higher with March at $ 1.56 -LCB- a bushel; soybeans were \ cent lower to 2 -LCB- cents higher with January at $ 5.76 -RCB- a Livestock and meat futures were mixed in early trading on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORG