 The stock market pushed ahead today, getting more mileage out of the rally it began on Tuesday. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials, up 23.89 points Tuesday, rose 16.43 to 2,768.56 by noontime today on Wall Street. That brought the average to within striking distance of the record closing high of 2,791.41 it reached on Oct. 9, before it took a 190-point drop four days later. Gainers outnumbered losers by about 7 to 5 in nationwide trading of <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> Exchange-listed issues, with 766 up, 536 down and 585 unchanged. Analysts said traders drew some encouragement from the <ORGANIZATION> Commerce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> report that retail sales rose 0.8 percent in November, exceeding advance estimates. But interest rates rose a bit following the news, and investors still seemed to be cautious about the outlook for the economy in 1990 and the prospect that corporate profits might remain weak. Energy stocks were actively traded, running into some resistance after their recent rally inspired by cold weather in many parts of the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and forecasts of higher oil prices in the months ahead. Among the volume leaders, <ORGANIZATION> Texaco </ORGANIZATION> rose -RRB- to 57 -LCB-; <ORGANIZATION> Unocal </ORGANIZATION> gained -RRB- to 31; <ORGANIZATION> Exxon </ORGANIZATION> added -LRB- to 51 -RRB-; <ORGANIZATION> Phillips </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Petroleum </ORGANIZATION> was unchanged at 25 ~, and <ORGANIZATION> Amoco </ORGANIZATION> slipped \ to 55 -RRB- In the blue-chip industrial sector, <ORGANIZATION> Philip </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morris </ORGANIZATION> rose -RRB- to 43 -LRB-; <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Telephone </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <ORGANIZATION> Telegraph </ORGANIZATION> | to 45 -RCB-, and <ORGANIZATION> Coca-Cola </ORGANIZATION> 1 -RRB- to 80 ~ The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks gained .96 to 195.40. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up 1.22 at 378.63. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 92.23 million shares at noontime, up from 77.62 million at the same point Tuesday.
