<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday dropped its debt ratings for <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and its financial subsidiary by one notch amid concern over vehicle sales, competition and capital expenditures. <ORGANIZATION> Fitch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Investors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said it was reviewing <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s securities and <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Poor </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said no change was likely Movement in security ratings indicate increasing or decreasing faith in the creditworthiness of a company. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s said in a news release that it was lowering a variety of <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> securities because of `` concerns that <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s operating performance will remain under pressure over the intermediate term,'' or three to four years. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s rating for <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s senior debt was lowered to `` Baa2'' from `` Baa1.'' <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s analyst <PERSON> Carol </PERSON> <PERSON> Verschell </PERSON> said that was toward the lower end of the company's investment-grade ratings. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Houston </PERSON> read a statement saying: `` We're disappointed in the action that <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s has taken But we believe that it will not have any material effect on Chrysler ... borrowing costs.'' <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s also said <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s share of the light truck market, which includes the company's popular minivans and Jeep vehicles, will come under increasing competitive pressure. <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION>'s announcement earlier this month to sell <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Technologies </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, which includes <ORGANIZATION> Gulfstream </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Aerospace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, will provide some cash, <PERSON> Verschell </PERSON> said, but the timing of the sale and the amount are uncertain. At <LOCATION> Fitch </LOCATION>, auto analyst <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Anne </PERSON> <PERSON> Sudol </PERSON> said her firm's ratings for a variety of <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> securities were either the same or slightly higher than <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s new ratings. All Chrysler ratings were under review, she said. `` There will be some action, but I do n't know when it will come,'' <PERSON> Sudol </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Nancy </PERSON> <PERSON> Stroker </PERSON> of <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's said her company affirmed the `` BBB'' rating of <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </ORGANIZATION> securities, roughly the same level as <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> 's </ORGANIZATION>. `` We do n't expect to have any kind of rating change,'' she said. <PERSON> Verschell </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s was not reviewing the ratings of <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> or <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> securities. <ORGANIZATION> Moody </ORGANIZATION>'s announcement of lower <ORGANIZATION> Chrysler </OR