<HEAD>Macy's Quarterly Loss Widens Due to Markdowns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> R.H. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> on Wednesday disclosed its financial losses grew significantly in the late summer and early autumn due to costs promotions aimed at boosting sales. The retailer said it lost $ 33.12 million, or $ 23.92 a share, in its first fiscal quarter of 1990, compared with a loss of $ 19 million, or $ 15 a share, in the same period a year earlier. Sales rose 5.2 percent to $ 1.71 billion in the three months ended Oct. 28 from $ 1.62 billion a year earlier. Macy, which went private in a leveraged buyout in 1986, disclosed the losses in a filing with the <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION>. In a separate letter to investors, <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Finkelstein </PERSON> described the retailing climate as `` chaotic'' and said the first quarter results were `` somewhat disappointing although essentially as expected.'' In the <ORGANIZATION> SEC </ORGANIZATION> filing, <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> attributed the first-quarter loss to the effects of `` increased markdowns taken in response to a highly competitive retail environment.'' `` We expect a sluggish economy this Spring but we are determined to run a profitable business, expensed conservatively with improved margins even with modest sales growth,'' read the letter, which was signed by <PERSON> Finkelstein </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> S. </PERSON> <PERSON> Handler </PERSON>. <PERSON> Macy </PERSON> opened two department stores during the quarter, although it said it does n't plan to open any others until 1991, when one new store is planned. `` That temporary hiatus of new store activity has a double benefit: we can concentrate our energies on improvement of stores already in operation and capital expenditures will be capped at levels significantly below plan, enhancing our cash flow,'' the letter read. <PERSON> Macy </PERSON> said losses from the <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Francisco </LOCATION> earthquake, which damaged its <ORGANIZATION> Macy </ORGANIZATION>'s <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> and <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> Magnin </PERSON> subsidiaries, did not impact the latest results.
